# Walkthrough: Map Integration for Riders

The Rider App now features a fully functional navigation system, replacing the static placeholders with interactive maps.

## Key Map Features

### 1. Interactive Navigation Map
- **Live View**: The "Maps Navigation" screen now uses **Apple Maps (iOS) or Google Maps (Android)** natively inside the app.
- **Rider Tracking**: A blue dot shows the rider's **exact real-time location**, helping them stay oriented during the delivery.

### 2. Pickup & Drop-off Markers
- **Mart Marker (Orange)**: Clearly marks the location of **Baldia Mart** for the order pickup.
- **Customer Marker (Green)**: Pinpoints the customer's delivery address for the final drop-off.
- **Visual Route**: A dashed line connects the pickup and drop-off points to give riders a clear visual of their journey.

### 3. External Navigation Support
- **🧭 Shortcut**: Added a new compass icon button in the header.
- **One-Click Link**: Clicking it immediately opens the current destination in the **dedicated Google Maps app** for turn-by-turn voice navigation.

## Verification
- [x] **MapView**: Verified the map renders and follows the rider's movement.
- [x] **Permissions**: Integrated `expo-location` to handle iOS/Android location permissions gracefully.
- [x] **Overlay Sync**: Items checklist now sits as a smart overlay on the map, so riders can see the route and products simultaneously.

---
*Riders now have all the tools they need to navigate safely and efficiently to our customers!*
